        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 24 at 3:50PM MDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 350 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 19
miles south of Maljamar, or 29 miles southwest of Lovington. This
thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Caprock, Maljamar, Lea County Zip Franklin Memorial Airport, Halfway,
and Loco Hills.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
